main event: A UFO sighting was reported in Datil, New Mexico on February 24, 1950, with a total of 7 accompanying photographs.
interesting points: The photographs show various bright and elongated objects, some resembling streaks or cylindrical shapes, against a dark background, suggesting they were taken at night or in low-light conditions.
One photograph depicts a small, bright teardrop-like shape against the dark background, while another shows a silhouette resembling a key hanging in mid-air against a light-colored background.
Two photographs display predominantly dark backgrounds with small bright spots, possibly light sources or objects in the night sky.
The images provide visual evidence of the reported UFO sighting, adding credibility to the witness account.
The handwritten numeral '6' is visible at the bottom left of one of the photographs, potentially indicating the order in which the images were taken or cataloged.
